22/07/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A special commission will investigate the cause of a fire Monday (July 21st) aboard a train travelling from Plovdiv to Sofia, the state railway company BDZ announced.
The blaze forced the evacuation of about 260 passengers and crew.
The railway reported no injuries.
In February, a train fire killed nine people and injured several more.
(BTA, Focus, Dnevnik, Mediapool, BTV, BNR - 21/07/08)
